WEBVTT

00:08.500 --> 00:09.667
[keys clacking]

00:09.667 --> 00:11.125
[typewriter dings]

00:11.125 --> 00:14.333
Are you gonna be weird
about last night?

00:14.333 --> 00:15.875
[squeals]
Probably.

00:15.875 --> 00:17.125
- [chuckles]
- You're not?

00:17.125 --> 00:19.041
Nope.
It was perfect.

00:19.041 --> 00:22.166
But  we'll take it slow.

00:22.166 --> 00:25.583
I will take it any way

00:25.583 --> 00:29.583
you want to give it to me.
- [giggles]

00:29.583 --> 00:31.959
You need to come back with
something no one's expecting.

00:31.959 --> 00:34.375
Do a show that will
make people go, "Shit.

00:34.375 --> 00:36.417
I didn't know
he could do that."

00:36.417 --> 00:38.667
- You guys gotta do it.
- We're a little busy

00:38.667 --> 00:40.083
helping to destroy
our current show.

00:40.083 --> 00:41.750
Hello!

00:41.750 --> 00:43.208
- Oh, bollocks!
- You know, I've never enjoyed

00:43.208 --> 00:44.625
- your cooking more.
- Hey!

00:44.625 --> 00:47.500
- Want to do a show?
- Whoo-hoo.

00:48.875 --> 00:52.208
Dear God,
what have we done?

00:52.208 --> 00:53.458
[llama grunts]

00:56.750 --> 00:58.750
[keys clacking]

00:58.750 --> 01:01.917
[typewriter dings]

01:01.917 --> 01:05.041
[wind blows]

01:10.000 --> 01:13.041
♪ quirky music ♪

01:13.041 --> 01:18.125
♪♪♪

01:36.667 --> 01:37.750
[gunshot]

01:45.458 --> 01:48.458
♪ light music ♪

01:48.458 --> 01:53.333
♪♪♪

01:55.750 --> 01:57.542
- Surprise!
- Look at you!

01:57.542 --> 01:59.125
Out of your house,
driving a car.

01:59.125 --> 02:02.792
- I know!
- Oh, it's like Lazarus.

02:02.792 --> 02:04.291
But with a better haircut.

02:04.291 --> 02:05.917
Oh.

02:05.917 --> 02:07.291
Who's Lazarus?

02:07.291 --> 02:08.625
From the Bible.

02:08.625 --> 02:09.375
And she had really bad hair?

02:09.375 --> 02:12.333
Yes, she
had really bad hair.

02:12.333 --> 02:12.625
God smote her with it.

02:12.625 --> 02:13.792
Ooh.

02:13.792 --> 02:16.667
- [chuckles]
- Aw.

02:16.667 --> 02:18.792
What a treat.

02:18.792 --> 02:20.500
Just to see you in sunlight.

02:20.500 --> 02:21.959
How did this happen?

02:21.959 --> 02:24.667
Um, A:
the shrink upped my Prozac.

02:24.667 --> 02:26.875
- [giggles]
- Never hurts.

02:26.875 --> 02:29.083
And...B?

02:29.083 --> 02:31.834
Who said there's a B?
[giggles]

02:31.834 --> 02:34.792
Your little friend, A.

02:34.792 --> 02:38.542
I'm...
kind of seeing somebody.

02:38.542 --> 02:40.458
You--you haven't
left your house in

02:40.458 --> 02:45.542
three weeks, unless
you ordered him on Amazon.

02:45.542 --> 02:47.166
Okay.
I'll tell you,

02:47.166 --> 02:49.458
but you can't
be judgmental.

02:49.458 --> 02:50.834
[scoffs]

02:50.834 --> 02:52.417
Why would I--

02:55.166 --> 02:58.166
How can you
be back with her?

02:58.166 --> 03:00.000
Have you forgotten how
controlling and paranoid--

03:00.000 --> 03:02.458
A: Judgmental.
- Well--

03:02.458 --> 03:04.333
And B: not her.

03:04.333 --> 03:06.000
- [scoffs]
- [sighs]

03:08.333 --> 03:09.250
Not Castor?

03:09.250 --> 03:10.333
Castor?

03:10.333 --> 03:11.834
- Oh--no.
- [sighs]

03:11.834 --> 03:13.834
[laughs]
Oh, God no.

03:13.834 --> 03:16.500
[both shudder]

03:16.500 --> 03:17.667
Well then...

03:17.667 --> 03:19.625
Nooooo...

03:19.625 --> 03:20.959
All right.
I know.

03:20.959 --> 03:22.041
I know what
you're going to say.

03:22.041 --> 03:23.208
Really?
I don't.

03:23.208 --> 03:26.000
You-you have actually...
[shaky breath]

03:26.000 --> 03:27.709
rendered me speechless.

03:27.709 --> 03:28.291
How could you possibly--

03:28.291 --> 03:30.125
So not so speechless.

03:30.125 --> 03:31.333
[stammers]

03:31.333 --> 03:33.208
I just don't--
of all the men--

03:33.208 --> 03:35.125
Excuse me,
men and women in the world.

03:35.125 --> 03:36.041
[mocking sounds]

03:36.041 --> 03:37.542
With Merc?
Lapidus?

03:37.542 --> 03:40.208
May I speak now?

03:43.166 --> 03:45.250
[mumbles]

03:48.709 --> 03:50.542
It's totally  different
this time.

03:50.542 --> 03:52.000
- [muffled]
- It is!

03:52.000 --> 03:55.291
It's like all the good stuff

03:55.291 --> 03:55.750
minus the bullshit.

03:55.750 --> 03:57.000
Mm-hmm?

03:57.000 --> 03:59.583
There's no Jamie, so...

03:59.583 --> 04:00.750
[laughs]

04:00.750 --> 04:02.750
I don't have to share him.

04:02.750 --> 04:04.500
We don't have to sneak around.

04:04.500 --> 04:05.417
Mmm, mm.

04:05.417 --> 04:07.083
He's not my boss anymore.

04:07.083 --> 04:08.500
And that's not a turnoff
for you?

04:08.500 --> 04:10.875
No.
[scoffs]

04:10.875 --> 04:13.750
Look, I--
[sighs]

04:13.750 --> 04:15.000
I know you're not a fan.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.625
- Mmm!
- But...

04:17.625 --> 04:21.125
I'm kind of starting
to feel like me again.

04:21.125 --> 04:22.709
Just a...

04:22.709 --> 04:24.250
And he's the reason.

04:24.250 --> 04:25.000
And a little bit
the Prozac,

04:25.000 --> 04:29.041
but mostly him, so...

04:29.041 --> 04:32.250
put away all your little
mmms and hmms

04:32.250 --> 04:36.125
and try
to be happy for me.

04:38.333 --> 04:39.667
All right.

04:39.667 --> 04:41.125
[inhales]

04:41.125 --> 04:43.000
If this is really
what you want...

04:43.000 --> 04:43.792
It is.

04:43.792 --> 04:46.166
...then I will

04:46.166 --> 04:48.542
try to support it.

04:48.542 --> 04:51.000
Really?

04:51.000 --> 04:51.417
Mm-hmm.

04:53.625 --> 04:54.750
Mm-hmm.

04:58.792 --> 05:00.959
Mmm...
[squeaks] hm!

05:00.959 --> 05:02.667
- ♪ lively music ♪
- Be here next time.

05:02.667 --> 05:04.375
We'll be one step closer
to finding out

05:04.375 --> 05:06.583
who will beat the box.

05:06.583 --> 05:09.834
[cheers and applause]
Good night!

05:09.834 --> 05:12.750
[cheers and applause]

05:15.291 --> 05:16.250
- Hey, bud.
- Hey.

05:16.250 --> 05:18.542
How's my favorite client?

05:18.542 --> 05:20.291
I don't know.
How is Bradley Cooper?

05:20.291 --> 05:22.625
[laughs] Well, you're
definitely my funniest.

05:22.625 --> 05:24.458
So listen, what if I told you

05:24.458 --> 05:26.041
that you could make
a million two

05:26.041 --> 05:28.417
and all you have to do is
spend a day in Philadelphia?

05:28.417 --> 05:30.166
Seriously?
A whole day?

05:30.166 --> 05:31.458
- QVT...
- Oh, Jesus.

05:31.458 --> 05:34.542
...wants you to front a line
of Matt LeBlanc vests.

05:34.542 --> 05:35.667
What are you trying to do
to me?

05:35.667 --> 05:37.250
1.2 if you sell out.

05:37.250 --> 05:38.875
Which is what I'd be doing.

05:38.875 --> 05:39.917
Oh, please.
You know who's doing QVT now?

05:39.917 --> 05:41.667
Hm?

05:41.667 --> 05:42.500
Everybody.

05:42.500 --> 05:43.834
Bradley Cooper?

05:43.834 --> 05:45.166
Don't do that.

05:45.166 --> 05:45.917
Jennifer Hudson's
selling pants.

05:45.917 --> 05:47.375
Your friend Ellen
is there.

05:47.375 --> 05:49.083
Give her a call,
she'll tell you.

05:49.083 --> 05:50.500
It's the easiest money
you will ever make.

05:50.500 --> 05:52.500
- 1.2 from vests?
- It's pure profit.

05:52.500 --> 05:53.625
They sell 'em for,
like, 39.99,

05:53.625 --> 05:56.792
but they cost a buck
to make in Sri Lanka.

05:56.792 --> 05:58.041
- What do I have to do?
- Nothing.

05:58.041 --> 05:59.166
You stand there
in your vest.

05:59.166 --> 06:01.291
You take a few calls.
You watch the tote board go up.

06:01.291 --> 06:02.625
It's like a telethon,
only you're the disease.

06:02.625 --> 06:04.500
How soon would this happen?

06:04.500 --> 06:05.458
As soon as the little children
finish sewing the buttons on.

06:05.458 --> 06:08.500
It's not really kids
making them, right?

06:08.500 --> 06:09.500
[laughs] No.

06:12.875 --> 06:14.208
- Hello.
- Hello.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.625
Hey, hey--
let me ask you something.

06:15.625 --> 06:17.542
Would you pay 39.99

06:17.542 --> 06:18.875
for this vest?

06:18.875 --> 06:20.542
First of all,
it's a waistcoat.

06:20.542 --> 06:23.417
[mocking imitation]

06:23.417 --> 06:26.291
Fine, would you pay 39.99
for this waistcoat?

06:26.291 --> 06:27.667
That particular one?

06:27.667 --> 06:29.375
No-no.
This is like 400 bucks.

06:29.375 --> 06:31.208
Like a shittier version
of this.

06:31.208 --> 06:32.375
So your question is
would I buy

06:32.375 --> 06:34.542
a shitty waistcoat
for 39.99?

06:34.542 --> 06:35.917
- Yeah.
- No.

06:35.917 --> 06:36.917
This-this is not
your target audience.

06:36.917 --> 06:39.333
Anyway,

06:39.333 --> 06:40.375
ready to go?

06:40.375 --> 06:42.208
Oh, right.
Big weekend.

06:42.208 --> 06:43.875
You guys gonna
bring me back a new show?

06:43.875 --> 06:45.250
- [chuckles] That's the plan.
- Fingers crossed.

06:45.250 --> 06:47.083
All right!
Go be funny.

06:47.083 --> 06:48.959
You go be agent-y.

06:48.959 --> 06:50.375
Ah, look,

06:50.375 --> 06:52.041
you already started.

06:52.041 --> 06:53.250
Think vests.

06:53.250 --> 06:55.000
All right,
let me just go, uh,

06:55.000 --> 06:56.250
change out of this,
and then we can--

06:56.250 --> 06:57.417
Hey, hey!

06:57.417 --> 06:58.792
What's that one doing here?

06:58.792 --> 07:00.458
- [Sean] Morning, hello.
- Hello.

07:00.458 --> 07:02.625
No one told me
about the reunion.

07:02.625 --> 07:04.000
- Oh, no-no-no.
- Oh, we're doing

07:04.000 --> 07:04.458
a new show together.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.834
Oh, exciting!

07:06.834 --> 07:08.750
Getting the old team
back together.

07:08.750 --> 07:10.166
Well, not the whole team.

07:10.166 --> 07:12.333
I'm totally kidding.

07:12.333 --> 07:13.291
We know.

07:13.291 --> 07:14.291
So what brings you here?

07:14.291 --> 07:17.083
Oh, just picking up
my man.

07:17.083 --> 07:18.208
- Picking up your--what?
- Sorry?

07:18.208 --> 07:20.250
Oh, yeah,
Mr. Lapidus and I

07:20.250 --> 07:21.834
are kind of an item.

07:21.834 --> 07:22.542
What-an item?
What--

07:22.542 --> 07:24.250
what do you mean by "item"?

07:24.250 --> 07:26.667
Are you shitting me?
Why?

07:26.667 --> 07:28.583
Uh, not everyone can be
the perfect boyfriend,

07:28.583 --> 07:30.875
guy who fucked my daughter
then never called her again.

07:30.875 --> 07:31.834
They gotta learn.

07:31.834 --> 07:34.250
[Beverly] You and...Merc?

07:34.250 --> 07:37.250
Well, you know we used to
have a thing back in the seven--

07:37.250 --> 07:38.834
Just say it.

07:38.834 --> 07:40.625
And you're back together now?

07:40.625 --> 07:41.875
Uh, yeah.

07:41.875 --> 07:44.000
In fact, as of last week--
[gasps]

07:44.000 --> 07:45.291
What's this?

07:45.291 --> 07:47.083
You're engaged?

07:47.083 --> 07:49.417
Oh, I love hearing it
with the accent.

07:49.417 --> 07:51.792
You're...engaged.

07:51.792 --> 07:53.291
I know,
it's kind of fast.

07:53.291 --> 07:55.667
But hey, no one's
getting any younger.

07:55.667 --> 07:57.458
You are.

07:57.458 --> 07:58.875
Ohh.

07:58.875 --> 08:00.417
And he gave you
that ring?

08:00.417 --> 08:01.959
[hushed]
I know!

08:01.959 --> 08:03.834
If the light catches it
just right,

08:03.834 --> 08:06.709
Merc Lapidus starts
looking pretty damn good.

08:09.959 --> 08:11.458
What a bastard.

08:11.458 --> 08:13.291
- Let it go.
- I can't.

08:13.291 --> 08:15.125
I always said
he was a dick.

08:15.125 --> 08:17.417
This is gonna kill her.

08:17.417 --> 08:20.667
I even feel bad
for Morning.

08:23.750 --> 08:25.041
Were those new tits?

08:25.041 --> 08:27.083
I know.
I thought that too.

08:27.083 --> 08:29.000
So we all feel bad
for Morning.

08:29.000 --> 08:29.917
Well, she'll be fine.

08:29.917 --> 08:32.583
She got the ring,
she'll get alimony.

08:32.583 --> 08:34.750
Meanwhile, poor Carol.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.583
If you could have
seen her face...

08:36.583 --> 08:38.375
she's so happy.

08:40.000 --> 08:41.500
Fucker.

08:41.500 --> 08:42.333
I don't know what
I'm gonna tell her.

08:42.333 --> 08:44.375
You're gonna
tell her nothing.

08:44.375 --> 08:46.250
That's what
you're gonna tell her.

08:46.250 --> 08:48.709
- Oh--I've gotta say something.
- No, you don't.

08:48.709 --> 08:52.125
You really wanna be the one
who brings her this news?

08:52.125 --> 08:53.458
There's a reason
"hug the messenger"

08:53.458 --> 08:55.041
is not an expression.

08:55.041 --> 08:57.500
So then I'm supposed
to let her just go on,

08:57.500 --> 09:00.000
completely oblivious?

09:00.000 --> 09:03.000
[car horn honks]

09:03.000 --> 09:05.875
It's not like
they were bigger...

09:05.875 --> 09:07.834
- Hmm.
- ...but there's...

09:07.834 --> 09:09.166
something.

09:09.166 --> 09:11.667
- Hands on the wheel.
- Yeah, I know.

09:11.667 --> 09:12.959
They were just more...

09:12.959 --> 09:14.375
hel-lo.

09:14.375 --> 09:15.291
I'm trapped in a car
with two boobs

09:15.291 --> 09:17.417
talking about tits.

09:17.417 --> 09:18.542
No, you're right.

09:18.542 --> 09:20.500
It's awful.
Poor Carol.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.041
It's like her nipples
looked higher.

09:25.041 --> 09:27.542
- They can do that?
- I'd like to think so.

09:27.542 --> 09:28.834
- I'm calling her.
- No, don't call her.

09:28.834 --> 09:30.583
Every time you've
got involved,

09:30.583 --> 09:32.667
every time--
am I wrong?

09:32.667 --> 09:34.250
So what?
[sighs]

09:34.250 --> 09:35.000
He just gets away with it?

09:35.000 --> 09:37.083
It's her life.
Stay out of it.

09:37.083 --> 09:39.417
[sighs]

09:39.417 --> 09:41.208
I hate this.

09:44.375 --> 09:45.083
It's probably just her bra.

09:45.083 --> 09:47.792
You think?

09:47.792 --> 09:49.959
Wardrobe told me she gets them
specially made in Brazil.

09:49.959 --> 09:51.250
Ooh.

09:51.250 --> 09:53.333
- Interesting.
- Good to know.

09:53.333 --> 09:57.083
[quirky music]

09:57.083 --> 10:01.291
♪♪♪

10:01.291 --> 10:04.375
Okay, this is it.
[clears throat]

10:04.375 --> 10:06.375
[Beverly] This is
your little ranch house?

10:06.375 --> 10:08.000
- Yee-haw!
- [giggles]

10:08.000 --> 10:10.000
Yeah, I had the set guys
from Friends  do it.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.458
I just said,
"Give me a ranch set."

10:11.458 --> 10:12.291
You're lucky there's
a fourth wall.

10:12.291 --> 10:14.750
- [sniffs]
- What?

10:14.750 --> 10:16.875
I was just
trying to place that...

10:16.875 --> 10:17.917
fragrance.

10:17.917 --> 10:18.250
Ah.
Horseshit.

10:18.250 --> 10:20.333
Ah.

10:20.333 --> 10:21.917
I was gonna guess
eucalyptus.

10:21.917 --> 10:23.375
Nope.
Horseshit.

10:23.375 --> 10:25.500
Although sometimes they shit
on the eucalyptus,

10:25.500 --> 10:26.375
so maybe that's it.

10:26.375 --> 10:28.000
Good nose, darling.

10:28.000 --> 10:29.458
Yeah, it's way worse
during the day.

10:29.458 --> 10:31.375
Mmm, something to
look forward to.

10:31.375 --> 10:33.291
- You guys want a drink?
- No, no, that's all right.

10:33.291 --> 10:34.125
It's been a long day.

10:34.125 --> 10:35.375
And we have a big,
smelly day tomorrow.

10:35.375 --> 10:37.291
[mutters]
Oh, well...

10:37.291 --> 10:39.500
Okay, grab your stuff.

10:39.500 --> 10:41.250
[Sean] Right behind you.

10:41.250 --> 10:43.667
- Breathe through your mouth.
- I'm trying.

10:43.667 --> 10:45.917
♪♪♪

10:45.917 --> 10:48.125
This is certainly
not what I expected.

10:48.125 --> 10:49.458
No.
It's like a sleepover

10:49.458 --> 10:51.041
at Michael Jackson's house.

10:51.041 --> 10:53.917
Ohh.

10:53.917 --> 10:56.333
- What?
- Look.

10:56.333 --> 10:59.250
- What?
- There.

11:01.041 --> 11:03.083
- What, the hair?
- Yes, the hair.

11:03.083 --> 11:04.291
These sheets
aren't clean.

11:04.291 --> 11:06.542
- Better?
- No.

11:06.542 --> 11:07.875
Ohh.
There's another one.

11:10.125 --> 11:12.583
[distant animal calls]

11:12.583 --> 11:15.000
Hey.
What's up?

11:15.000 --> 11:17.500
Uh...

11:17.500 --> 11:19.500
I think whoever's
in charge of the beds

11:19.500 --> 11:21.333
may have forgotten to

11:21.333 --> 11:23.792
change our sheets.

11:23.792 --> 11:25.250
That'd be Lupe.

11:25.250 --> 11:26.041
Yes, well,

11:26.041 --> 11:28.166
Lupe forgot
to change our sheets.

11:28.166 --> 11:31.333
You sure?

11:31.333 --> 11:33.166
There were hairs in mine.

11:33.166 --> 11:33.667
Ah, I wouldn't
worry about it.

11:33.667 --> 11:35.542
It's just my kids.

11:35.542 --> 11:37.166
Uh...
they were gray.

11:37.166 --> 11:38.583
Gray and...

11:38.583 --> 11:40.667
[clears throat]
curly.

11:40.667 --> 11:42.917
Oh,
and my mom stayed here.

11:42.917 --> 11:44.458
So she doesn't
color all her hair.

11:44.458 --> 11:47.125
Ew.
Fucking Lupe.

11:47.125 --> 11:49.250
I'll talk to her on Monday.

11:49.250 --> 11:51.208
Yeah.

11:51.208 --> 11:53.709
But, uh, in-
in the meantime...

11:53.709 --> 11:55.291
- Hmm?
- [exhales]

11:55.291 --> 11:57.458
I'm-I'm sure your mother
is perfectly hygienic,

11:57.458 --> 11:59.208
but call me crazy...

11:59.208 --> 11:59.875
And I do.

11:59.875 --> 12:01.875
...I prefer clean sheets.

12:01.875 --> 12:03.125
So, uh, if you'll just

12:03.125 --> 12:04.792
show me where the linens
are...

12:06.166 --> 12:07.583
I don't know
where the linens are.

12:07.583 --> 12:09.208
How do you not know
where the linens are?

12:09.208 --> 12:11.250
- It's your ranch.
- I know where the barn is.

12:11.250 --> 12:12.542
- Probably cleaner.
- I'm sorry, what?

12:12.542 --> 12:15.458
So when you need
to change your sheets...

12:15.458 --> 12:17.208
Lupe does it.

12:17.208 --> 12:18.709
- Or not.
- Well, do you wanna switch?

12:18.709 --> 12:20.625
- Take my bed.
- No. [exhales]

12:20.625 --> 12:22.375
Those are your dirty sheets.

12:22.375 --> 12:23.750
I don't know what
to tell you.

12:23.750 --> 12:27.875
♪♪♪

12:32.083 --> 12:32.542
So?

12:32.542 --> 12:33.792
Totally useless.

12:33.792 --> 12:36.208
You're welcome to
scooch in here with me.

12:36.208 --> 12:37.834
What makes you think
yours are any cleaner?

12:37.834 --> 12:38.875
You're welcome
to sleep on top of me.

12:38.875 --> 12:41.250
Maybe I can
flip the sheets over.

12:41.250 --> 12:42.792
Darling, I'm begging you,

12:42.792 --> 12:43.917
just turn off the light
and let's go to sleep.

12:43.917 --> 12:46.208
[sighs] Fine.

12:46.208 --> 12:47.375
But I'm not getting undressed.

12:47.375 --> 12:49.083
Perfect.
Do that.

12:49.083 --> 12:50.500
[sighs]

12:52.250 --> 12:54.041
Sleep well.

12:54.041 --> 12:55.125
[mutters]

12:56.417 --> 12:59.417
[low whirring sound]

13:01.375 --> 13:03.250
Brilliant.

13:03.250 --> 13:05.625
[sighs]

13:05.625 --> 13:06.625
[typewriter keys clacking]

13:06.625 --> 13:07.917
[typewriter dings]

13:12.000 --> 13:14.959
How the fuck do they
sleep in outer space?

13:14.959 --> 13:17.834
Well, for one thing,
they have clean sheets.

13:19.458 --> 13:20.709
[gunshots]

13:20.709 --> 13:23.166
[gasps]
Holy shit.

13:28.000 --> 13:28.500
[lightsaber activates]

13:28.500 --> 13:29.959
[lightsaber hums]

13:33.625 --> 13:35.125
[softly]
What the fuck?

13:35.125 --> 13:37.083
You hear that?

13:37.083 --> 13:37.500
The gunshots?

13:37.500 --> 13:39.625
No, listen.

13:39.625 --> 13:41.750
[crickets chirping]

13:44.500 --> 13:45.792
Something's
definitely out here.

13:45.792 --> 13:49.834
So you just shot
randomly into the night?

13:49.834 --> 13:51.375
Didn't you say
you have a ranch hand?

13:51.375 --> 13:53.125
- Yeah.
- Maybe you don't anymore.

13:53.125 --> 13:55.792
No, it's this wild boar
that's been coming around.

13:55.792 --> 13:56.542
A wild boar?

13:56.542 --> 13:58.208
I fucking hate that pig.

13:58.208 --> 14:01.750
He digs holes everywhere,
eats my sprinkler heads.

14:01.750 --> 14:03.333
Shits on the pool furniture!

14:03.333 --> 14:05.041
How do you know
it's always the same pig?

14:05.041 --> 14:06.458
Oh, I know those shits.

14:06.458 --> 14:07.875
I think I might have
winged him.

14:07.875 --> 14:09.709
We should go check.
[Beverly] You go check.

14:09.709 --> 14:11.583
- We're not going out there.
- It's fine.

14:11.583 --> 14:14.083
To face the potentially
wounded wild boar?

14:14.083 --> 14:16.000
Just, here-here.
Grab a shovel.

14:16.000 --> 14:17.500
No, I'm not grabbing a shovel.

14:17.500 --> 14:19.375
Nothing good ever starts
with "Grab a shovel."

14:19.375 --> 14:20.834
All right, fine.

14:20.834 --> 14:22.041
I'll go alone.

14:22.041 --> 14:23.625
So you should.
It's your boar.

14:23.625 --> 14:25.542
I'm coming for you,
fucker!

14:25.542 --> 14:27.667
[distant animal calls]

14:27.667 --> 14:28.875
[lightsaber deactivates]

14:28.875 --> 14:30.250
[Beverly]
It's like having a sleepover

14:30.250 --> 14:32.917
with No Country for Old Men.

14:32.917 --> 14:36.000
♪ quirky music ♪

14:36.000 --> 14:38.750
♪ ♪

14:38.750 --> 14:39.792
[Matt] Morning.

14:39.792 --> 14:40.875
- Mm.
- Morning.

14:40.875 --> 14:42.041
I made coffee.

14:42.041 --> 14:43.542
- Oh, I could use some.
- Sounds good.

14:43.542 --> 14:45.542
I think there's
bagels in the freezer.

14:45.542 --> 14:47.208
Maybe some eggs.

14:47.208 --> 14:48.542
Oh, my God.

14:48.542 --> 14:49.542
Did you know
your gun

14:49.542 --> 14:51.959
is still sitting out here
next to the cereal?

14:51.959 --> 14:54.000
Oh, and there's cereal.

14:54.000 --> 14:55.542
[laughs]

14:56.333 --> 14:58.375
Find any dead bodies
in your yard?

14:58.375 --> 15:01.875
No. But that fucking pig
knocked over my barbecue.

15:01.875 --> 15:02.917
There's irony.

15:02.917 --> 15:06.208
[phone rings]

15:06.208 --> 15:06.500
[sighs] Carol.

15:06.500 --> 15:08.375
Huh.

15:08.375 --> 15:10.333
Hello.

15:10.333 --> 15:12.208
Hey.
How's the ranch?

15:12.208 --> 15:13.959
Very ranch-y.

15:13.959 --> 15:15.208
Yeah?

15:15.208 --> 15:17.125
Like someone lit
a horseshit candle.

15:17.125 --> 15:18.417
I told you,
soon as the sun hits it,

15:18.417 --> 15:20.625
oof.

15:20.625 --> 15:22.250
Question.

15:22.250 --> 15:23.750
It's Merc's birthday
next week,

15:23.750 --> 15:27.041
and A: I have no idea
what to get him.

15:27.041 --> 15:30.417
Also, B: I've got no money
to get it with.

15:30.417 --> 15:32.917
Then I say, C:
fuck him.

15:32.917 --> 15:36.917
Is it too lame
if I make something?

15:36.917 --> 15:38.083
- I have got to tell her.
- I was thinking, like,

15:38.083 --> 15:42.208
going to one of those
Color Me Mine places

15:42.208 --> 15:45.250
and making a little bowl.

15:45.250 --> 15:46.458
So what do you think?

15:46.458 --> 15:47.750
I think

15:47.750 --> 15:48.834
making something for him
is fine.

15:48.834 --> 15:51.000
- I just...
- Beverly.

15:51.000 --> 15:53.750
...wouldn't put your
heart into it.

15:53.750 --> 15:54.542
'Ello, Beverly.

15:54.542 --> 15:56.458
He's there?

15:56.458 --> 15:56.917
Mm-hmm.

15:56.917 --> 15:58.250
All right, well,

15:58.250 --> 15:59.625
got to get to work.

15:59.625 --> 16:00.625
Wish him happy birthday
for me.

16:00.625 --> 16:02.250
[chuckles]
Bye.

16:04.792 --> 16:07.000
I am the worst person
ever.

16:07.000 --> 16:08.125
[gun cocks]

16:08.125 --> 16:09.625
[imitates gunshot]

16:09.625 --> 16:12.625
Second worst.

16:12.625 --> 16:15.625
Okay, I had my assistant
get us pads,

16:15.625 --> 16:17.291
pens, scissors, Post-its.

16:17.291 --> 16:19.000
She got us a white board.

16:19.000 --> 16:20.625
You name it,
it's all here.

16:20.625 --> 16:23.000
Jesus. It's like she
knocked over a Staples.

16:23.000 --> 16:25.959
- Oh, fuck, staples!
- I wouldn't worry.

16:25.959 --> 16:27.792
I don't think we'll
get so much done

16:27.792 --> 16:30.625
that we'll need to
attach things to each other.

16:30.625 --> 16:32.333
Okay, glass half empty.

16:32.333 --> 16:34.875
So do you have any sense
of the kind of show

16:34.875 --> 16:36.000
you want to do?

16:36.000 --> 16:37.792
I'm thinking a one-hour.

16:37.792 --> 16:39.333
I don't know,
something smart.

16:39.333 --> 16:41.166
Maybe a little dark.

16:41.166 --> 16:41.625
You know, sophisticated.

16:41.625 --> 16:43.542
Anything else?

16:43.542 --> 16:44.125
In an ideal world,

16:44.125 --> 16:45.834
I get to shoot people.

16:45.834 --> 16:49.417
That is sophisticated.

16:49.417 --> 16:50.667
[Beverly] So...
[exhales]

16:50.667 --> 16:52.375
we've got...

16:52.375 --> 16:53.959
smart,

16:53.959 --> 16:57.542
so-phis-ti-cated...

16:59.250 --> 17:00.000
Shoots people.

17:00.000 --> 17:03.166
- Ooh! I got an idea.
- Go.

17:03.166 --> 17:03.709
Can I do the writing
on the board?

17:03.709 --> 17:04.834
Absolutely.

17:04.834 --> 17:07.917
- That was your idea?
- Yep.

17:07.917 --> 17:09.875
Okay, so what's the show?
Let's just toss things out.

17:09.875 --> 17:11.709
Anything's fair game.

17:11.709 --> 17:12.542
There are no bad ideas.

17:12.542 --> 17:14.792
Okay.

17:16.333 --> 17:18.500
What if I'm the president?

17:18.500 --> 17:19.834
Of what planet?

17:19.834 --> 17:20.917
I thought there
were no bad ideas.

17:20.917 --> 17:22.000
- So did I.
- Screw you.

17:22.000 --> 17:23.667
I could play a president.

17:23.667 --> 17:25.458
Okay, let's say
you're the president.

17:28.291 --> 17:29.709
So, now we have

17:29.709 --> 17:31.709
smart, sophisticated,

17:31.709 --> 17:33.709
shoots people,

17:33.709 --> 17:34.583
and president.

17:34.583 --> 17:37.041
I'm liking this.

17:37.041 --> 17:38.125
Should I make
a reservation for lunch?

17:38.125 --> 17:40.166
- We just started.
- I know.

17:40.166 --> 17:41.417
But
the way we're moving...

17:41.417 --> 17:43.208
Okay, so,

17:43.208 --> 17:44.375
you're the president.

17:44.375 --> 17:46.125
- Then what?
- I don't know.

17:46.125 --> 17:47.250
You're the writers.
I gave you president.

17:47.250 --> 17:50.166
If I could do it all,
I wouldn't need you.

17:50.166 --> 17:52.208
Ooh!

17:52.208 --> 17:54.166
What if I come back
from the dead?

17:54.166 --> 17:55.000
Are you still the president?

17:55.000 --> 17:55.834
No, no, new idea.

17:55.834 --> 17:57.208
All right.

17:57.208 --> 17:57.792
But what I do come back
from the dead with?

17:57.792 --> 17:59.041
Like superpowers

17:59.041 --> 18:02.667
or, uh, some kind
of special knowledge?

18:02.667 --> 18:04.542
Maybe you come back
with an idea for a show.

18:04.542 --> 18:05.959
Or clean sheets.

18:05.959 --> 18:09.208
Okay, I'm getting a real
negative vibe here.

18:09.208 --> 18:10.750
[Beverly]
Where you going?

18:10.750 --> 18:11.542
I need a cookie.
Anyone else want a cookie?

18:11.542 --> 18:13.583
No, come back,
attention span.

18:13.583 --> 18:15.750
You're the board guy.
You have the pen.

18:15.750 --> 18:18.083
[sighs] Fine.

18:18.083 --> 18:20.083
Has anyone ever done
sort of a

18:20.083 --> 18:22.500
Sliding Doors  kind of thing,

18:22.500 --> 18:25.083
where you see three iterations
of a man's life

18:25.083 --> 18:27.917
different ways
they could have gone.

18:27.917 --> 18:30.083
You could intercut
between them,

18:30.083 --> 18:32.083
see how they inform each other.

18:32.083 --> 18:34.375
- Or what if I'm a pimp?
- Or what if you're a pimp?

18:34.375 --> 18:35.542
Well, seriously.

18:35.542 --> 18:38.583
It could be this
cool, dark, edgy show.

18:38.583 --> 18:40.291
I'm a slimeball,

18:40.291 --> 18:42.875
but I care about my girls.

18:42.875 --> 18:44.792
Actually, I don't think
we've ever

18:44.792 --> 18:45.959
seen that world before.

18:45.959 --> 18:47.250
Documentaries, maybe.

18:47.250 --> 18:48.792
Yeah, totally, totally.

18:48.792 --> 18:51.709
I could run, like, this
bunny ranch in the desert.

18:51.709 --> 18:54.625
And we could explore how each
of the girls ended up there.

18:54.625 --> 18:56.208
Learn about them as people.

18:56.208 --> 18:59.166
Yeah, dig into the
little nuances of their lives.

18:59.166 --> 19:00.291
Oh!
[huffs]

19:00.291 --> 19:00.417
I got a title.

19:05.750 --> 19:07.583
[Beverly] Whores.

19:07.583 --> 19:08.625
There's your nuance.

19:08.625 --> 19:09.959
I love this.

19:09.959 --> 19:11.291
[Sean]
What are you doing?

19:11.291 --> 19:12.625
Pitching it to Roger.

19:12.625 --> 19:14.375
Whoa-whoa-whoa.
Slightly premature.

19:14.375 --> 19:15.792
Oh, nah, this is it.

19:15.792 --> 19:17.291
I would totally watch
Whores.

19:17.291 --> 19:20.667
I think we're all
assuming that you have.

19:20.667 --> 19:22.250
Hey, it's me.

19:22.250 --> 19:23.166
Guess what?

19:23.166 --> 19:25.041
We got a show.

19:25.041 --> 19:27.291
It's a dark,
edgy one-hour

19:27.291 --> 19:28.834
about a brothel
in the desert,

19:28.834 --> 19:30.709
and it's called...

19:30.709 --> 19:31.834
Yeah.
He guessed Whores.

19:31.834 --> 19:33.875
He knows you well.

19:33.875 --> 19:34.834
What? No.

19:34.834 --> 19:36.041
That sucks.

19:36.041 --> 19:38.041
Netflix
is already doing Whores.

19:38.041 --> 19:39.125
Are you sure?

19:39.125 --> 19:42.041
Treat Williams
and Sharon Stone.

19:42.041 --> 19:43.500
Jesus.

19:43.500 --> 19:45.709
All right.
I'll talk to you later.

19:46.875 --> 19:48.166
Shit.

19:48.166 --> 19:49.542
Oh, I understand
your disappointment,

19:49.542 --> 19:53.500
having invested almost
four minutes of your life.

19:53.500 --> 19:54.166
Fucking Netflix.

19:54.166 --> 19:56.166
I know it's hard
to believe,

19:56.166 --> 19:58.667
but there might be
one other idea

19:58.667 --> 19:59.000
in the universe.

19:59.000 --> 20:00.959
No, I-I-

20:00.959 --> 20:01.834
I can't do this now.
I need a break.

20:01.834 --> 20:03.000
From what?

20:03.000 --> 20:04.083
Let's go shoot something.

20:04.083 --> 20:05.583
Like, what?
A one-hour?

20:05.583 --> 20:06.458
Come on, seriously.
You ever fired a gun?

20:06.458 --> 20:08.709
I couldn't even fire
our assistant.

20:08.709 --> 20:10.125
♪♪♪

20:10.125 --> 20:11.041
[Beverly sighs]

20:11.041 --> 20:14.500
Spread your feet
a little more.

20:14.500 --> 20:16.250
Don't lock your knees.

20:16.250 --> 20:17.375
[horse whinnying distantly]

20:17.375 --> 20:19.792
Is it gonna be loud?
I don't like loud.

20:19.792 --> 20:20.709
- Nah, you're fine.
- You promise?

20:20.709 --> 20:22.375
Yeah, it's like
slamming a car door.

20:24.709 --> 20:27.000
And, uh, now get your grip
a little higher.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.834
Make sure your support hand
is against the weapon as well.

20:29.834 --> 20:30.875
Oh, when did John Hinckley
get here?

20:30.875 --> 20:32.959
When I was a boy,
my father took me shooting.

20:32.959 --> 20:34.208
You never told me.

20:34.208 --> 20:35.875
Yeah.
It was my mother's idea.

20:35.875 --> 20:37.417
She thought it would
bring us closer.

20:37.417 --> 20:38.834
Turns out it just
made me realize

20:38.834 --> 20:39.750
how easy it would be
to kill him.

20:39.750 --> 20:41.458
- [chuckles]
- All right, less talking,

20:41.458 --> 20:43.125
more aiming.
Now, you want to loosen up.

20:43.125 --> 20:44.375
Don't hunch your shoulders.

20:46.125 --> 20:48.083
Still hunching.

20:48.083 --> 20:49.959
Still hunching.

20:50.750 --> 20:51.875
Still hunching

20:51.875 --> 20:52.959
Those are my shoulders!

20:52.959 --> 20:53.917
Really?

20:55.583 --> 20:57.250
Now, you want to have both hands
tight on the grip--

20:57.250 --> 20:59.917
- [gunshot]
- It's loud! It's loud!

20:59.917 --> 21:01.709
- It's loud! It's loud!
- [gun firing]

21:01.709 --> 21:03.542
- It's loud! It's loud!
- [bottles smashing]

21:03.542 --> 21:04.792
[hysterical sounds]

21:04.792 --> 21:05.375
Holy shit.

21:05.375 --> 21:07.166
Well done, darling.

21:07.166 --> 21:09.208
That was no fucking car door.

21:09.208 --> 21:10.458
All right, all right,
just give me the weapon.

21:10.458 --> 21:11.875
I am never doing this again

21:11.875 --> 21:14.250
because [shouting]
it...was...loud!

21:14.250 --> 21:15.333
- Okay.
- All right, my turn.

21:15.333 --> 21:16.750
- [loudly] What?
- My turn!

21:16.750 --> 21:18.041
[muttering]

21:19.583 --> 21:21.291
All right, now, remember.
Focus on the sights,

21:21.291 --> 21:23.375
- not the target.
- Don't worry, I remember.

21:23.375 --> 21:24.333
[Matt clears throat]

21:25.291 --> 21:26.917
- [gunshot]
- [Beverly whimpers]

21:26.917 --> 21:29.959
I was just warming up.

21:29.959 --> 21:31.500
[gun fires]

21:31.500 --> 21:32.750
I got to remember to breathe.

21:32.750 --> 21:33.792
[gun fires]

21:33.792 --> 21:35.458
[chuckles]

21:35.458 --> 21:37.750
This weapon's heavier
than my father's.

21:39.500 --> 21:41.250
- [gunshot]
- [Beverly whimpers]

21:41.250 --> 21:42.959
I think there's something
wrong with your gun.

21:42.959 --> 21:44.959
Don't hunch
your shoulders.

21:44.959 --> 21:46.125
Shh...

21:46.125 --> 21:49.000
Just relax.
You can do it.

21:49.000 --> 21:49.959
Feeling a lot of pressure.

21:49.959 --> 21:50.458
Use it.

21:55.291 --> 21:56.333
[gun fires]

21:56.333 --> 21:56.834
[animal squeals]

21:56.834 --> 21:57.959
What the hell?

21:57.959 --> 22:00.625
[animal squealing]

22:00.625 --> 22:03.417
[grunting, squealing]

22:04.083 --> 22:06.500
- [laughs]
- Oh, no!

22:06.500 --> 22:07.792
[Sean] No-no-no-no-no.

22:07.792 --> 22:09.792
- [Beverly] Oh, God.
- What did I do?

22:09.792 --> 22:10.417
You got the fucker.

22:10.417 --> 22:12.166
I didn't mean to get him.

22:12.166 --> 22:13.375
Oh, look at the poor
thing!

22:13.375 --> 22:15.375
- I can't-I can't look!
- Oh!

22:15.375 --> 22:16.709
It's suffering.

22:16.709 --> 22:18.000
- Well, I know how to stop that.
- [cocks gun]

22:18.000 --> 22:19.417
Wha-what are you doing?

22:19.417 --> 22:20.834
I'm gonna finish it off.
This is him.

22:20.834 --> 22:21.542
- Is it?
- You don't know that.

22:21.542 --> 22:23.458
Well, who do you
think it is?

22:23.458 --> 22:25.875
You just ate your last
sprinkler head, asshole!

22:25.875 --> 22:27.041
- No!
- What?

22:27.041 --> 22:28.792
You can't kill this pig.

22:28.792 --> 22:31.000
So he eats a few
bloody sprinkler heads.

22:31.000 --> 22:32.625
He has as much right
to live here as you do.

22:32.625 --> 22:35.959
Uh, as the guy who paid
8 million for it...

22:35.959 --> 22:37.834
If this were a dog,

22:37.834 --> 22:38.333
would you shoot a dog?

22:38.333 --> 22:40.000
It's not a dog.

22:40.000 --> 22:41.542
Yes, well,

22:41.542 --> 22:44.000
did you know that
pigs are more intelligent

22:44.000 --> 22:45.834
than dogs,
and quite a few people?

22:45.834 --> 22:47.500
Yeah? Then how come
I'm the one with the gun?

22:47.500 --> 22:49.000
- Oh--
- And when did you become

22:49.000 --> 22:50.333
the fucking pig expert?

22:50.333 --> 22:53.333
When I was growing up,
my cousins had pet pigs.

22:53.333 --> 22:56.083
Oh, they are the
most loyal, affectionate,

22:56.083 --> 22:58.083
emotionally sophisticated--

22:58.083 --> 23:00.291
Oh, it's shitting!

23:00.291 --> 23:01.041
- [groans]
- Oh, this is horrible!

23:01.041 --> 23:03.125
Just end it!
End it!

23:03.125 --> 23:04.000
No!

23:04.000 --> 23:06.208
This is Wilbur!

23:06.208 --> 23:08.083
In Charlotte's Web,
this is...

23:08.083 --> 23:10.250
that talking pig movie.

23:10.250 --> 23:11.208
- Babe?
- Yes!

23:11.208 --> 23:12.542
He's gonna shoot Babe.

23:12.542 --> 23:13.083
[gasps]
You can't shoot Babe.

23:13.083 --> 23:14.917
It's not Babe.

23:14.917 --> 23:15.750
It's bacon.

23:15.750 --> 23:17.208
Oh.

23:17.208 --> 23:18.709
Hey, if this
was a talking pig,

23:18.709 --> 23:20.125
we'd be having
a very different conversation,

23:20.125 --> 23:21.583
all four of us.

23:21.583 --> 23:23.458
Just because you
can't understand him

23:23.458 --> 23:24.625
doesn't mean
he's not communicating.

23:24.625 --> 23:25.792
Other pigs understand him.

23:25.792 --> 23:28.250
I understand him,
right now.

23:28.250 --> 23:31.208
He's saying,
"I'm in pain, help me!"

23:31.208 --> 23:32.375
We need to help him!

23:32.375 --> 23:33.792
No.
You know what we need?

23:33.792 --> 23:36.417
Hash browns.

23:36.417 --> 23:39.041
We need to get him
to a vet.

23:39.041 --> 23:40.667
What?
No. It's a wild boar.

23:40.667 --> 23:41.667
You're a wild boar!

23:41.667 --> 23:43.208
Where was that snappy dialogue

23:43.208 --> 23:44.709
when we were working before?

23:44.709 --> 23:47.291
Oh, look,
it's passed out.

23:47.291 --> 23:48.417
We are taking this animal
to a doctor.

23:48.417 --> 23:50.709
We are not taking him
to a doctor.

23:50.709 --> 23:52.083
All right.

23:52.083 --> 23:54.083
Then you're on your own
with your stupid show.

23:54.083 --> 23:54.875
- Oh, come on.
- That's right.

23:54.875 --> 23:56.333
I am putting it-
we are putting it

23:56.333 --> 23:59.458
all on the line
for this pig.

23:59.458 --> 24:01.542
You want us?

24:01.542 --> 24:02.709
The pig comes too.

24:02.709 --> 24:05.917
[scoffs]
Fuck me.

24:05.917 --> 24:07.333
I'll get the truck.

24:07.333 --> 24:08.125
[keys clacking]

24:08.125 --> 24:09.667
[typewriter dings]

24:09.667 --> 24:12.667
[sighs] All right,
let's fucking do this.

24:12.667 --> 24:15.500
Uh, you guys get the back,
I'll get the front.

24:15.500 --> 24:18.542
[boar groaning]

24:18.542 --> 24:20.000
- [yelps]
- [both] What?

24:20.000 --> 24:20.375
I touched the tail!

24:20.375 --> 24:22.000
Switch.

24:26.625 --> 24:27.458
[Matt] Okay, ready?

24:27.458 --> 24:29.166
One, two,

24:29.166 --> 24:30.625
three.
Pick it up.

24:30.625 --> 24:31.917
- [all strain]
- Pick it up. Pick it up.

24:31.917 --> 24:33.083
- Now what?
- Put it down.

24:33.083 --> 24:34.291
Put it down. Put it down.

24:34.291 --> 24:35.625
- Ah!
- Ooh!

24:35.625 --> 24:37.750
Fuck, that's a heavy pig.

24:37.750 --> 24:38.750
- Ideally, we need a winch.
- Oh, sure.

24:38.750 --> 24:41.291
We could just make one
out of sticks and twigs.

24:41.291 --> 24:43.333
- Do you have a ramp?
- What am I, Angie's List?

24:43.333 --> 24:45.583
There's no time.
His breath is getting shallow.

24:45.583 --> 24:46.291
That's not what I'd call it.

24:46.291 --> 24:48.125
We've got to
do something now!

24:48.125 --> 24:50.625
Uh...I know.

24:50.625 --> 24:52.500
I can accidentally
back over it.

24:52.500 --> 24:54.875
Let's just try
lifting it again.

24:54.875 --> 24:56.125
- We can do this.
- I don't think--

24:56.125 --> 24:57.041
- We've got to.
- All right.

24:57.041 --> 24:58.709
All right, okay, okay,
how about this?

24:58.709 --> 24:59.750
You take the front,

24:59.750 --> 25:00.667
you take the back,

25:00.667 --> 25:03.375
and I'll get the middle.

25:03.375 --> 25:04.709
Okay.

25:05.750 --> 25:08.667
[Matt] One, two,

25:08.667 --> 25:09.542
three!

25:09.542 --> 25:11.667
[all straining]

25:14.083 --> 25:16.500
Ow. Ow.

25:16.500 --> 25:18.083
The bristles are
going through my gloves.

25:18.083 --> 25:19.166
Keep going.

25:19.166 --> 25:20.834
Hurts. Hurts.

25:20.834 --> 25:21.750
You're tipping.

25:21.750 --> 25:23.250
I know I'm tipping!

25:23.250 --> 25:24.917
[groans]

25:26.333 --> 25:29.000
I hate this fucking pig.

25:29.000 --> 25:31.458
♪ quirky music ♪

25:31.458 --> 25:33.667
Why is this taking so long?

25:33.667 --> 25:36.333
You shot him up
pretty good.

25:36.333 --> 25:37.834
I'm sure he'll be fine.

25:37.834 --> 25:39.750
He lost so much blood.

25:39.750 --> 25:41.875
[dog whines]
[sheep bleats]

25:41.875 --> 25:42.667
It's funny.

25:42.667 --> 25:43.917
When you have ham,

25:43.917 --> 25:47.875
there's like
no blood at all.

25:47.875 --> 25:48.333
Hmm.

25:48.333 --> 25:50.458
What? It's true.

25:50.458 --> 25:53.041
[animals whining]

25:53.041 --> 25:53.667
How is he?

25:53.667 --> 25:56.125
I wish I had better news.

25:56.125 --> 25:56.917
The bullet tore
through an artery

25:56.917 --> 25:58.667
and also punctured
his trachea.

25:58.667 --> 26:02.208
So much a talking pig.
[chuckles]

26:02.208 --> 26:03.417
Will he survive?

26:03.417 --> 26:05.166
It's possible.
He's a fighter.

26:05.166 --> 26:06.166
- Oh, thank God.
- The good news is

26:06.166 --> 26:08.917
we were able
to stop the internal bleeding.

26:08.917 --> 26:10.291
Okay.

26:10.291 --> 26:12.375
Tracheal reconstruction
is more complicated.

26:12.375 --> 26:14.375
- But it's doable?
- Well, it's tricky.

26:14.375 --> 26:16.291
It means taking cartilage
from either his ear

26:16.291 --> 26:17.709
or his thyroid.

26:17.709 --> 26:19.667
I'm not sure we
could do that here.

26:19.667 --> 26:21.375
We'll probably have to
move him to a larger facility.

26:21.375 --> 26:23.709
Say we do all that,

26:23.709 --> 26:25.083
what kind of prognosis
can we hope for?

26:25.083 --> 26:27.166
Well, obviously
there are no guarantees,

26:27.166 --> 26:28.417
but I think with time

26:28.417 --> 26:29.333
he stands a good chance
of recovery.

26:29.333 --> 26:32.250
Oh, that's such a relief.

26:32.250 --> 26:33.458
Thank you.

26:33.458 --> 26:35.250
How much are we
talking here?

26:35.250 --> 26:36.792
It's hard to say.

26:36.792 --> 26:38.250
Minimum, 12 to 15,000.

26:38.250 --> 26:41.542
You paying?

26:43.333 --> 26:45.250
- Well, we did what we could.
- He had a good life, it's...

26:45.250 --> 26:49.041
♪ quirky music ♪

26:49.041 --> 26:51.458
♪ ♪

26:51.458 --> 26:54.458
♪ somber music ♪

26:54.458 --> 27:00.583
♪♪♪

27:03.625 --> 27:05.750
[phone ringing]

27:11.917 --> 27:13.000
Okay...

27:13.000 --> 27:13.583
[phone ringing]

27:13.583 --> 27:16.375
Oh...
[sniffles]

27:16.375 --> 27:18.792
oh.

27:18.792 --> 27:20.125
[muttering]

27:20.125 --> 27:22.542
[phone ringing]

27:22.542 --> 27:24.000
[groans, spits]

27:24.000 --> 27:25.625
[gagging]

27:25.625 --> 27:26.291
Uh, hold on.

27:26.291 --> 27:28.750
Oh...

27:33.542 --> 27:34.709
[spits]
Bah!

27:40.208 --> 27:41.291
Hello?

27:41.291 --> 27:41.917
Are you okay?

27:44.792 --> 27:46.375
Uh-huh.

27:46.375 --> 27:49.041
[keys clacking]

27:49.041 --> 27:52.041
♪ quirky music ♪

27:52.041 --> 27:56.917
♪♪♪
